column2: Sunny- east wind at 5 mph- ice out a week ago.  Macrophtytes green and grows a new path constructed on 50% of north shoreline.
North wind at 5 mph and 0% cloud cover.
The bottom is 6.5'- 10% cloud cover and 5 mph from the north.
500 Ft off curly leaf pondweed around shoreline.  Clear and sunny with a SW to NE 3 mph wind.
West wind at 5 mph and 30% cloud cover.
Rained last night- 40% cloud cover and west to east wind at 5 mph.  Three families out- catfish- good size yellow bullheads- Bluefill and sunfish.
Indian lake is nearly completely covered with rooted weeds.
Lake is nearly completely covered with weeds.
The entire lake is covered with weeds.
The lake is covered with rooted aquatic weeds.
East wind at 7 mph- 80% cloud cover and new lake aerator installed.
Bottom at 6.8 Ft.  Northwest wind at 2-5 mph.
Harvester working on lake- calm- 50% cloud cover.
Boat movement not a problem where weeds were harvested- 75% cloud cover- wind @ 5 mph from w- 5 boats on the lake.
Alyssa Boge helped me collect the data.  It was cloudy and windy.  There was lots of seaweed floating on the top of the water.
Alyssa Boge helped collect data.  Lots of seaweed in the water.  Clear sky.  Two blue herons spotted.
I monitored with Alyssa Boge.  We spotted two great blue herons and we shared the lake with a canoer.  It was partly cloudy- partly windy- and sunny.  There was lots of seaweed and water bugs.
Seaweed covers lake water around edges- partly cloudy
Monitored with Alyssa Boge.  Lots of algae and seaweed- cloudy- still water-  two herons spotted- two fishermen- two sandhill cranes spotted- first day after the rain stopped.
very windy- some seaweed under water- lots of people on shore fishing- walking- etc.
clear skies- dog walkers- geese- turkey vultures
cloudy- slightly windy- dog walkers- water very high and murky from mud after rains
water very high- seaweed blooms- clear skies- no wind- fishermen- waterbugs- birds
water is lower than before- much more seaweed than there was
cloudy- warm- windy- clearer water than previous date
clear skies- still- slight breeze- warms- lots of seaweed throughout the lake- murky near shore
cloudy- windy- sunny- many people at park- dog walkers- picnicers
very windy- dog walkers- partly cloudy
overcast- still water- birds out- slightly windy
slightly windy- birds- hawk- lots of visitors- clear skies- storm night before
slightly windy- overcast- warm- fish jumping out of water
weather: mostly sunny- 75 degrees- 50 percent humidity- NNE wind at 10 mph
2014 ice-out date for Indian Lake was April 9.
Warnings posted around lake for blue-green algae outbreak.
Observations follow week of heavy rain.
Blue-green algae outbreak on lake. May be starting to dissipate- but west end of lake and Halfway Prairie creek (outlet flowing west) have significant algae.
Water quality improved from last year. Invasive carp received rotenone treatment under the ice on March 3- 2015: http://dnr.wi.gov/news/releases/article/?id=3516
More vegetation/weeds than previous years. Friends group planted native aquatic plants on July 11- 2015 in two areas along west and north shore.
Water lilies- sedges- etc from July 11 planting are doing well.

Lake vegetation has gradually disappeared from surface after highest density in early to mid-July. Herons appear to be fishing for newly stocked fish- also a kingfisher on the north shore. Herons and sandhill cranes are commonly seen this summer.
Water still appears murky and green but is less murky and less green than any previous Indian Lake survey this year.
User perception of water quality is about 3.5.
Deepest secchi disk reading in several years. Water is noticeably much clearer. Great blue heron fishing at southwest corner of lake.
Thick mats of curly-leaf pondweed on west end of lake- difficult to row boat.
Two significant changes since last survey on June 19- 2016: major dieback of curly-leaf pondweed and decrease in water clarity. Bald eagle soaring over lake at 3 pm.
Curly-leaf pondweed has completely disappeared from lake. This area received about 4 inches of rain in past 4 days.
Flushed great blue heron on southwest shore of lake. Water quality appears to be lowest of the summer.
Great blue heron on west end of lake. Several great egrets in eastern bay- one on west end. Friend swam in lake this morning and reported good water quality.
For the Perception category it was difficult to decide between 3 (slightly impaired) and 4 (substantially reduced). If I had the choice I'd say 3.5- medium impaired.
Help from Laura Cominetti. Wind picked up once on the lake- causing low swells.
Last spring (2016) also the lake was clearer than usual. Curly-leaf pondweed and Eurasian watermilfoil have spread in the past two weeks.
Geese (with goslings) and ducks on lake- and tree swallows over the water. Vegetation (duckweed- milfoil) out to 15 feet from shore. 86 degrees F and humid.
For SECCHI DEPTH- clarity was less than 1/8 of a foot- thus 0 if rounded to nearest quarter. Lake very murky- strong algae smell- no longer much vegetation.

column1: Under USER PERCEPTION OF WATER QUALITY- 4 is entered- but the actual value is between 4 (Would not swim but boating OK) and 5 (Enjoyment substantially impaired).
